E
fountain marble basin~
The fountain is a large circular affair made from blocks of carved white
marble. The decorations and embellishments on the rim of the basin are
impressive although a little florid and overstated. In the middle stands
a tall statue out of which fresh, clear water flows.
~
S
#2002
North Market Square~
   You are standing in a broad expanse that constitutes the northern portion
of Lamman's market square.  To the north you see Monastery Road lead north
out of town.  The huge Temple of Lamman is to the northeast.  Somewhat to
the west, you can make out the entrance to the Warrior's Widow, reputed to
offer the finest lodgings in town.  Just to the south you can see the large
central fountain surrounded, as always, by a throng of adventurers taking
a well-earned break.
~
