#2005
West Market Square~
   The flagstones that pave the Lamman Market Square are probably the most
heavily trodden on real estate in the entire archipelago.  All around you
there is activity.  As you stand here, you brush shoulders with a wide range
of people, everyone from wealthy merchants to poor tramps and beggars.  You
hear the soothing babble of water dancing in a large marble fountain to the
east.  The Market Square extends off to the north and south, while a small
courtyard opens up to the west between the Warrior Widow Inn and a bakery.
~
