S
#2006
The Temple Offices~
   This is the rather impressive entry hall to the offices of the temple
clery.  There are tapestries and fine paintings adorned on the walls
containing the illustrious history of the temple.  The entrance into the
High Priest's inner sanctum, to the north, is an archway of alternating dark
and light marble blocks, and filligree and scrollwork covering much of the
stone.  The temple offices exits south.
~
