S
#2007
Northeast Market Square~
   The busy market square of Lamman is filled with activity and noise.  There
are people everywhere you turn, each face unrecognizable from the last.
Everyone is busy running around on some errand, or busy hawking something you
may not need.  Loaming above this chaos, is the orderly Temple of Lamman to
the north.  Set up in this corner of the market are quite a few lending tables
set up by usurers interested in making quite a bit of money by bilking temple
worshippers and pilgrims of their gold.  Pauper's Row lies to the east.  The
market continues south and west.
~
