S
#2014
The Foyer of the Warrior's Widow Inn~
   This is the plush entry hall of the Warrior's Widow.  Small paintings of
slain heroes and dead fighters adorn the walls, their memories kept alive
here in this small gallery.  Also on the wall is a well-detailed map of
the city.  Scattered around the room are a few rickety tables and chairs of
unvarnished pine.  More tables and chairs can be found in the inn's bar and
restaurant to the north.
   A set of stairs leads up to the lodgings reception, if you want a room for
the night, that is where you should go.  The inn exits south onto a quaint
little road, and east onto the northwest part of Market Square.
~
20 12 0
