E
stairs staircase~
   A narrow wooden staircase leads up from the foyer.  The staircase looks
worn and in need of repairs, but luckily it will not collapse any time soon.~
E
wall walls gallery~
   You see a few paintings and a map on the bare brick walls, perhaps you
should take a look at them?~
E
painting paintings~
   Most of these paintings are crudely rendered portraits of famous dead
adventurers.  Some you may even recognize, but most you will not.  Under
each portrait is a name.  You see the names of <insert names here>.
   There also some paintings of legendary heroes who after wonderous deeds
and other labors, were raised to immortality.  There are names as innoculous
as Xero, and as pompous as Magnifico.  You also see the names of Ponder,
Kalliste, Saladin and Pulgh, heroes as old as, well, as old as you can imagine.~
S
#2015
The Commons Room of the Warrior Widow Inn~
   This place is just bustling with activity.  There are several buxom
serving lasses running about carrying foaming mugs of ale and mead.  Several
merchants are here getting pretty drunk.  The city watch also likes to pop
in here every so often, for a quick libation.  Nearby, the bartender is
polishing a pewter mug while eavesdropping in on various conversations for
any juicy information that he can later sell to the secret police.  The
common room exits south into the foyer, and west into the inn's kitchens.
~
