S
#2017
At the foot of the Temple Steps~
   Brightly polished marble steps lead up to the magnificent Temple of Lamman.
Many citizens of this fair city traipse up this rather grandiose staircase to
pay homage to the various deities that make their puny mortal lives worth
living.  To the south, the hustle and bustle of commerce, takes place out on
market square.  To the north, the ornate entrance to the temple offices can
be seen.  Before you take another step in any direction, you notice a squarish
block of polished granite embedded in the ground.  The stone is handsomely
inscribed with a map to aid those unfamilar with the layout of this fine city.
~
