#2042
Coutts' Royal Bank of Lamman~
   The stately black marble floor and the gilded fixtures and ornaments makes
the interior of this bank seem to exude wealth.  This is where citizens of
Lamman can bank their hard won crowns.  To ensure the safety of the wealth of
the citizenry, the King has posted two of his Royal Guard here.  A door on
the western wall, leads to the bank manager's office.  An open arched doorway
exits to the road to the north.
