thick stone wall of the bridge, you relax a little and view the picturesque
bay to the south.  You see many ships of many sizes and shapes, many of which
come from exotic locales.  From distant lands they sail to Lamman conveying
valuable cargoes and information.  At the mouth of the bay, you see the Lamman
Lighthouse; it is there to safely guide these ships into port.  Harbour Road
runs east into Market Square, and over the bridge west toward the Quay.
