#2096
Courtyard Lane~
   Your ears are filled with the resounding echoes of the clomping of horse
hooves and the stomping of adventurers' boots as you move along this narrow,
high-walled lane.  Contributing to the reverberations is the important
looking marble facade of the Royal Post Office of Lamman, the entrance to
which can be gained by going north.  Courtyard Lane continues to the east
toward the Market Square and west to the River Ronnan.
~
